---
import FeatureCard from "./ui/FeatureCard.astro";
import MiniCode from "./ui/MiniCode.astro";
---

<section class="py-24 bg-bg-base">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="text-center mb-12 reveal">
      <p class="section-label">The small things</p>
      <h2 class="mb-4">Sharp edges, filed down.</h2>
      <p class="body-lg mx-auto text-text-secondary">
        You will run this dozens of times a day. Every rough edge matters.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div
      class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 max-lg:grid-cols-2 max-sm:grid-cols-1"
    >
      <FeatureCard title="Natural language dates" class="reveal" data-delay="0">
        <MiniCode slot="code">
          <span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">oru</span>
          <span class="sub">add</span>
          <span class="str">"Ship v2"</span>
          <span class="flag">--due</span>
          <span class="val">tomorrow</span>
        </MiniCode>
        Parse "tomorrow", "friday", "next week", or any date string. No rigid formats
        required.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Context view" class="reveal" data-delay="80">
        <MiniCode slot="code">
          <span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">oru</span>
          <span class="sub">context</span>
        </MiniCode>
        See what needs attention right now – overdue tasks, in-progress work, and
        what's actionable next.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Task dependencies" class="reveal" data-delay="160">
        <MiniCode slot="code">
          <span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">oru</span>
          <span class="sub">add</span>
          <span class="str">"Deploy"</span>
          <span class="flag">--blocked-by</span>
          <span class="val">3</span>
        </MiniCode>
        Block tasks until prerequisites are done. Filter to actionable work with
        <code>--actionable</code>.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Labels" class="reveal" data-delay="0">
        <MiniCode slot="code">
          <span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">oru</span>
          <span class="sub">list</span>
          <span class="flag">--label</span>
          <span class="val">backend</span>
        </MiniCode>
        Tag and filter tasks. Labels are freeform strings – no predefined categories
        to manage.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Pipe-friendly" class="reveal" data-delay="80">
        <MiniCode slot="code">
          <span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">oru</span>
          <span class="sub">get</span>
          <span class="val">1</span>
          <span class="flag">--json</span> | <span class="cmd">jq</span>
          <span class="str">'.due'</span>
        </MiniCode>
        Non-interactive by design. Compose with jq, grep, and scripts – or let
        your agent call it directly.
      </FeatureCard>

      <FeatureCard title="Shell completions" class="reveal" data-delay="160">
        <MiniCode slot="code">
          <span class="prompt">$ </span><span class="cmd">oru</span>
          <span class="sub">completions</span>
          <span class="val">bash</span>
          | <span class="val">zsh</span>
          | <span class="val">fish</span>
        </MiniCode>
        Tab-complete commands, flags, and values. Ships with scripts for bash, zsh,
        and fish.
      </FeatureCard>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
